	)
	(text_box "Overview:\n\nThis circuit implements the standard Dynamixel (DXL) half-duplex UART-to-TTL conversion. It allows a standard full-duplex UART interface to communicate over a single-wire bus.\n\nTechnical Reference:\n\n  - Buffer IC: Utilizes the 74LVC2G241 for its 5V-tolerance and high-speed 3-state outputs, serving as a level-shifter for 3.3V MCUs.\n  - Directional Logic: The TX_EN signal (TP18) controls the data flow direction.\n  - Transmit Mode (High): Enables the transmit buffer and disables the receiver to prevent echo.\n  - Receive Mode (Low): Tri-states the transmitter and enables the receiver for incoming data.\n  - Bus Termination: Includes a 10k pull-up to 5V on the DATA line as per the reference standard.\n  - Reference Design: ROBOTIS e-Manual: DYNAMIXEL Selection Guide (TTL)."
		(exclude_from_sim yes)
		(at 209.55 29.21 0)
		(size 72.39 64.77)
		(margins 0.9525 0.9525 0.9525 0.9525)
		(stroke
